1
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:40,967
<i> You came right on time.</i>

2
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,700
<i>I just finished cooking dinner.</i>

3
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,167
<i> You cooked my favorite!</i>

4
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,567
<i>Here, these are from
the Philippines.</i>

5
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,867
<i> Just reheat it, Manuel.</i>

6
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,767
<i>This business wouldn't
have grown,</i>

7
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:51,700
<i>if it weren't for
the trust of a good friend.</i>

8
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> Thank you, Noah.</i>

9
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,833
<i>I also want to
thank my children.</i>

10
00:00:57,967 --> 00:01:00,167
<i> You're Jeffrey Cruz, right?</i>

11
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:01,167
<i> How did you know?</i>

12
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,700
<i> My mom told me who you are.</i>

13
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:03,733
<i> She said...</i>

14
00:01:03,867 --> 00:01:05,600
<i>- you're my dad.
- Tetay?</i>

15
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:07,133
<i>- Daisy?
- Let's go!</i>

16
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,667
<i> She could be your child!</i>

17
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,933
<i>What kind of person are you?
You're shameless!</i>

18
00:01:11,067 --> 00:01:12,733
<i> Hello? What?</i>

19
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,567
<i>I love them so much,
especially my mom.</i>

20
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,100
<i>I want to see her one last time.</i>

21
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:19,400
<i>Mom, can Daddy and I
go with you?</i>

22
00:01:19,533 --> 00:01:22,200
<i>Manuel, we're just going home to
the Philippines</i>

23
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,700
<i>for my mom's funeral,
nothing else.</i>

24
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,133
<i>Do you still think about Manuel?</i>

25
00:01:25,267 --> 00:01:26,833
<i>My relationship with him ended a
long time ago.</i>

26
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:28,967
<i>But we haven't even started
a relationship yet.</i>

27
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,867
<i> I feel bad about it.</i>

28
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:33,500
<i>I will wait until
you learn to love me.</i>

29
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,533
Yes, bro. I'm at the address
you gave me.

30
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:53,167
You said I would see a gate by
the green store.

31
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,367
<i>Yes, the place is full of
plants.</i>

32
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:55,400
<i> The green gate.</i>

33
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:56,867
<i> The one across the school.</i>

34
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Across the school?

35
00:01:58,133 --> 00:01:59,067
I see the school on the left
side of the street.

36
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,900
<i>Yes, it's by the store painted
in green.</i>

37
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:03,467
Yes, that's right.

38
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:40,067
Tetay, be good at school, okay?

39
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:40,833
Okay, Mom.

40
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:43,367
Would you like me to escort
you to your classroom?

41
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,667
You don't need to do that,
I can go there myself,

42
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,700
I'm a big girl now.

43
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:47,500
- Are you sure?
- Yes, Mommy.

44
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:48,567
Okay, then.

45
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,000
Wait for me after school, okay?

46
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:51,233
- I will come and get you.
- Okay.

47
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:08,167
Sweetie,
what do you want to order?

48
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:10,000
Mocha frappe, please.

49
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,267
What did Jessica want to order?

50
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,600
Mocha frappe.

51
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,467
Okay.

52
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,367
Okay, What would
you like to eat?

53
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,067
<i>Miss, can I have
a sweet cheese bun?</i>

54
00:03:29,967 --> 00:03:31,167
<i> Three please.</i>

55
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:34,767
<i>- My favorite!
- You guys have one each.</i>

56
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,533
<i> And save one for your mom.</i>

57
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,167
<i> Coleen can't have any yet.</i>

58
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,133
<i> What about you, Dad?</i>

59
00:03:41,267 --> 00:03:42,633
<i> Don't worry about me.</i>

60
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:44,967
<i>Just seeing you full
makes me happy.</i>

61
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:47,100
<i> You're so sweet, Daddy.</i>

62
00:03:47,233 --> 00:03:49,833
<i> Thank you, Dad.</i>

63
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:53,267
Manuel.

64
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,300
What would you like to eat?

65
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,533
Manuel!

66
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:03,900
What?

67
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:06,867
- What do you want to order?
- Sweet cheese bun.

68
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,300
What do you want to drink?

69
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,300
I'll have some black coffee.

70
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,433
One black coffee.

71
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:21,567
And a sweet cheese bun.

72
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:25,333
You know what, sis?

73
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:26,700
- Oh?
- I notice something,

74
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,267
between you and Noah.

75
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:29,900
You two are being
so sweet with each other.

76
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,267
What else are you looking for?

77
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,767
He's a good man, handsome,
and rich!

78
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,133
And he likes you and
accepts your children.

79
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:40,567
Despite your past.

80
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,967
So, what else are
you looking for?

81
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:43,867
I don't see anything wrong with
him.

82
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,933
Oh!

83
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,733
So, nothing's wrong with him.

84
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:50,700
Then, there must be something
wrong with you.

85
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:55,767
Don't tell me your heart still
belongs to your ex-lover, Felma?

86
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,633
Oh no, I feel nothing for him.

87
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:01,467
Whatever. Seriously?

88
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:03,200
- Yes.
- Tell me the truth.

89
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,433
- That's true.
- Okay, sis. Be honest with me.

90
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:06,967
What if you see him right now?

91
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,700
What are you going to do?
Tell me.

92
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,133
Stop this nonsense.

93
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:16,600
- My kids are waiting for me.
- Oh! Change topic!

94
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,067
Whatever.

95
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,667
Mocha frappe...

96
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,367
Are you in a rush?
You're going to leave me behind.

97
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,133
Love?

98
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:47,033
Manuel.

99
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:49,167
Manuel!

100
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:50,833
What's wrong with you?

101
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:52,500
I've been calling your name.

102
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,000
Let's go to the grocery store
after we eat.

103
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:57,167
I need to get stocks for the
wake, okay?

104
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,533
Okay.

105
00:06:00,467 --> 00:06:01,233
You're in a daze.

106
00:06:02,533 --> 00:06:03,567
Is my order ready?

107
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,367
So you went to Daisy's place.

108
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,300
Why didn't you talk to her?

109
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:21,200
Because he got scared, Mom.

110
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:28,133
I was nervous, okay?

111
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:30,900
I don't know
how to approach them.

112
00:06:33,133 --> 00:06:34,500
Excuses, excuses.

113
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:37,100
Just admit it,
you're just like your dad,

114
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:38,567
who abandoned his own family.

115
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,133
Don't compare me to your dad.

116
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,533
It's your dad!

117
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,733
Who's the wuss between us two?

118
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:44,667
You don't even get into any
relationship?

119
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,667
Because of what he did.

120
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,000
Why? Did I ever deny how I feel?

121
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:48,633
I don't ever get into any
relationship,

122
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:49,367
because I'm scared to be
abandoned

123
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,600
just like what your dad did

124
00:06:51,733 --> 00:06:53,767
and like what you are doing with
your daughter and Daisy now!

125
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:54,967
That's enough!

126
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,433
You're starting to get
on each other's nerves!

127
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:02,067
And please...

128
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:05,067
leave your dad out of this!

129
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,300
It's Andrea's fault.

130
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,667
She kept bringing her dad into
our conversation.

131
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,567
He's your dad!

132
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,500
Our dad!

133
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,567
I said, that's enough!

134
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:17,100
Aren't we discussing
Daisy and Tetay?

135
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:19,267
Why do you keep
involving your dad?

136
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,833
Haven't you moved on
from him yet?

137
00:07:23,667 --> 00:07:25,267
It's been eighteen years!

138
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,367
I'm sorry to say this.

139
00:07:35,467 --> 00:07:36,900
It's starting to get
on my nerves!

140
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:38,733
Whenever we're discussing
an issue,

141
00:07:38,867 --> 00:07:40,567
you always get him involved.

142
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,933
You guys have to stop.

143
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,633
Go on.

144
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,367
Let's eat our meal in peace.

145
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,400
Thank you.

146
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:19,300
What are you doing here?

147
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:22,800
Hazel, we just want to
apologize.

148
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:25,300
I will never forgive you.

149
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:26,633
Hazel.

150
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:28,867
Manuel.

151
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:32,533
You know
what they've done to me.

152
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,267
I went abroad.

153
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:45,867
I did everything to make
your life better.

154
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:47,700
What did you do in return?

155
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,867
They spent all
my hard-earned money.

156
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:57,400
Hilda, get them out of here.

157
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,867
Come, let's go out this way.

158
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:14,667
Hazel, perhaps you can listen to
what they have to say.

159
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,833
They've been begging for your
forgiveness.

160
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:18,400
We're still in Saudi back then.

161
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,767
It's hard for me
to forgive them.

162
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,100
I understand that it's hard.

163
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,067
But it's not impossible.

164
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,033
Forgiveness is a decision.

165
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:32,200
If you want to, you can forgive
them.

166
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,500
Hazel, they're your family.

167
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:37,200
You don't need to go back to
how things used to be.

168
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:41,267
What's important is for yoyu to
reconcile.

169
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:48,233
Hazel, I've sent them away.

170
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:01,233
Call them back.

171
00:10:03,367 --> 00:10:04,767
Tell them...

172
00:10:06,267 --> 00:10:08,067
I wanted to talk to them.

173
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:09,833
Okay.

174
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:21,833
Sis, here's the document for
the accounting.

175
00:10:21,967 --> 00:10:23,200
Just give this to them.

176
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:24,433
Thank you.

177
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:25,767
- Sis.
- Oh?

178
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:30,567
The Pinoy Moms asked about
the interview again.

179
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:31,900
What should I tell them?

180
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:35,033
I haven't decided yet.

181
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,900
Can we talk about this later?

182
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:38,533
Okay, Sis.

183
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:39,800
I'm gonna get going now.

184
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:40,833
- Okay.
- See you tomorrow.

185
00:10:40,967 --> 00:10:42,300
Thank you, sis.

186
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,433
- Bye, Noah.
- Bye.

187
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,300
What did I just hear,
Pinoy Moms?

188
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:49,733
Felma, you have to accept it.

189
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:55,100
Did you know that Pinoy Moms
have 1.2 million subscribers

190
00:10:55,233 --> 00:10:56,433
in ViewTube..

191
00:10:56,567 --> 00:11:01,733
It's a good platform to
promote our product.

192
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,600
I'm a bit hesitant.

193
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,233
They only want to know

194
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,800
about my past relationship with
Manuel.

195
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:13,600
I'm sure they'll focus
the interview on him.

196
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:16,533
Then, steer it back to business.

197
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:19,400
You know what, I'll give you
some pointers

198
00:11:19,533 --> 00:11:21,033
on how to guide the interview

199
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:22,533
on what you want to talk about.

200
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:26,467
It will be hard for me.

201
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:29,300
Because whenever Manuel become
the topic,

202
00:11:29,433 --> 00:11:30,800
I get triggered.

203
00:11:31,367 --> 00:11:32,400
Just like what happened last
night.

204
00:11:32,867 --> 00:11:34,367
The kids are talking
about him again.

205
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,367
It makes my blood boil!

206
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,867
Felma, he's been
a part of your life.

207
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,233
Every now and then,
his name will come up.

208
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,867
It shouldn't affect you.

209
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:49,467
You know...

210
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,633
You know what I think?

211
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,333
I think you haven't
forgiven him yet.

212
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:54,833
How did you say that?

213
00:11:55,767 --> 00:11:57,500
Because if you have forgiven
him,

214
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:01,900
It wouldn't affect you whenever
you talk about him.

215
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:32,533
I've always seen mom as this
tough, strong woman.

216
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,967
I never thought she could
forgive

217
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:38,400
Uncle Mario and Uncle Mikoy.

218
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:41,400
But she did.

219
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:43,700
Because of you, Dad.

220
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:48,500
You helped her realize
how important forgiveness is.

221
00:12:53,867 --> 00:12:56,433
I kind of noticed that
you seem sad.

222
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,167
Why?

223
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:01,567
What?

224
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:04,600
Oh, no. I was just thinking
that...

225
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:08,700
if your mom hasn't forgiven
them...

226
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:11,300
They will carry their sin for
the rest of their lives.

227
00:13:12,167 --> 00:13:14,033
That would've been awful.

228
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:18,300
I can't imagine being
in their position.

229
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:24,000
Knowing someone I love
chooses not to forgive me.

230
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:29,400
Here comes your cousins.

231
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,233
You want to meet them, don't
you?

232
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:33,433
Come on, let's meet them.

233
00:13:33,767 --> 00:13:34,767
I'll follow along.

234
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:35,933
Okay.

235
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:51,700
Manuel, thank you.

236
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:54,033
Hazel forgave us because of you.

237
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,967
Hello, Manuel.

238
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,000
You're here in the Philippines?

239
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:19,967
<i> Yes, I am, Bro.</i>

240
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,833
Hazel's mom died.

241
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:24,167
Oh really?
My condolences, Bro.

242
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,033
Thank you, Bro.

243
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:29,133
Bro, can you do me a favor?

244
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,233
Could you tell me Felma's
phone number and address?

245
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:34,900
Come on, Bro.

246
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:38,233
Didn't we already talk about
this before I left Saudi Arabia?

247
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:40,600
I don't want to be the bridge on
your family anymore, Bro.

248
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:41,733
Please, Bro.

249
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,467
Just her phone number.

250
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,633
I can't do that.

251
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:46,667
I don't want to get beaten up
by Paz, Bro.

252
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,100
Don't bother them anymore, Bro.

253
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:50,067
Felma and the kids are doing
well.

254
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,567
Don't bother them anymore.

255
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:53,667
Bro, I won't bother them.

256
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,367
I just want to see them.

257
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,767
My goodness! Fine,
if you want an update?

258
00:14:58,267 --> 00:15:00,533
Felma's business is growing.

259
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:01,667
The children are doing well.

260
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,167
Don't bother them anymore.

261
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,167
Oh really?

262
00:15:05,867 --> 00:15:07,800
What kind of business?
Is she still making longanisa?

263
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:09,533
Yes, she's still making them.

264
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,467
And Bro, just leave them be.

265
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,267
Don't bother them anymore, bye.

266
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:18,133
You want to talk to Felma?

267
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:31,400
Manuel, my mom just died!

268
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:34,133
You're still thinking about
Felma?

269
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,100
What kind of man are you?

270
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,567
Don't you have any
consideration?

271
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,233
You're so insensitive!

272
00:15:42,067 --> 00:15:45,233
Hazel, I just want to talk
to Felma and my kids.

273
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:46,867
So that we can also reconcile.

274
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,867
Just like you have forgiven
your siblings.

275
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,767
There!

276
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:51,000
So that's the reason,

277
00:15:51,133 --> 00:15:52,867
why you want me
to forgive my siblings?

278
00:15:53,667 --> 00:15:54,967
You have an ulterior motive.

279
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:58,433
You want to reconnect with
Felma!

280
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:01,933
Manuel, my issue with my
siblings,

281
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:03,567
is different from your issue
with your ex!

282
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,533
Hazel, can't you understand
my situation?

283
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:06,933
Eighteen years!

284
00:16:09,033 --> 00:16:10,267
Eighteen years had passed,
Manuel.

285
00:16:11,733 --> 00:16:13,167
They've moved on already.

286
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,900
You need to move on, too.

287
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:18,067
- Hazel, Hazel...
- Cut it out!

288
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:20,167
Don't ever try to see Felma!

289
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:21,900
Do you understand?

290
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:25,067
Don't ever try to see Felma!

291
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,200
You have to do as I say,
because I'm your wife!

292
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:03,900
<i> Sorry, Hazel.</i>

293
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,733
<i>I just want to ask
my family for forgiveness.</i>

294
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,900
Mom, I'm glad you agreed to get
interviewed by Pinoy Moms.

295
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:18,733
What kind of pictures do they
need?

296
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:21,133
Anything will do.

297
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:25,200
But they also want to see old
pictures.

298
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:30,300
Before we bacame successful in
life.

299
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:36,300
Look at this.

300
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:37,667
Oh?

301
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,300
This was from elementary and
high school.

302
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:42,667
That's your big brother and
big sister.

303
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:07,300
I thought I had this thrown out.

304
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,967
I asked Jeffrey
to throw this away.

305
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,233
No, Mom.

306
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:15,567
I asked Jeffrey
to throw this out!

307
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:16,533
Jeffrey!

308
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:17,800
I'm the one who kept those
pictures.

309
00:18:17,933 --> 00:18:18,867
I kept it.

310
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,300
I took it when Jeffrey
threw it out.

311
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:26,900
Coleen!

312
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:30,967
I'm sorry, Mom.

313
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:33,933
I didn't get to see dad in
person.

314
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:37,733
That's why I only look at him in
that picture.

315
00:18:40,033 --> 00:18:42,100
Your dad abandoned us a long
time ago

316
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,800
So you have to forget
about him, too.

317
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,733
Mom.

318
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:05,333
Is dad the reason why we don't
go to Luntian Park anymore?

319
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,867
Yes, sweetie.

320
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:17,033
That was a very special place
for us.

321
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:20,000
That place.

322
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:25,167
But ever since...

323
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:28,700
he cheated on me...

324
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:33,233
and abandoned us...

325
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,500
<i> Manuel is now my husband.</i>

326
00:19:36,033 --> 00:19:38,633
<i>Stop calling my husband "Love".</i>

327
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:39,833
<i>What do you mean by your
husband?</i>

328
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,567
<i> Yes, Manuel is now my husband.</i>

329
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,933
<i>- Hello, Love.
- Don't you ever call me "Love"!</i>

330
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,100
<i>He wanted to marry me,
do you hear me?</i>

331
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:49,733
<i>Because I'm pregnant!
He got me pregnant!</i>

332
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:56,567
I can't bear it.

333
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,833
I can't bear...

334
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,067
to go back to that place.

335
00:20:05,367 --> 00:20:09,367
I can't even get near it.

336
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:19,800
Mom?

337
00:20:22,567 --> 00:20:26,200
Can I keep these pictures?

338
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,667
I will keep it in my room...

339
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:31,567
so you won't see it.

340
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:38,633
Is it okay?

341
00:20:39,633 --> 00:20:41,133
Can we just not?

342
00:20:43,467 --> 00:20:44,567
Please?

343
00:21:09,567 --> 00:21:12,133
It's so hot here in the
Philippines, Mom.

344
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,267
I need to shower all the time.

345
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,267
I know, right?

346
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,400
I'm glad that we're going back
to Canada tomorrow.

347
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:23,900
Oh, wait.

348
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:25,733
Where's your dad?

349
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:27,933
He left, he said he had
to go somewhere.

350
00:21:28,967 --> 00:21:29,833
Where is he going?

351
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:32,500
I didn't ask him, Mom.

352
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,200
<i>Don't you have
any consideration for me?</i>

353
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:39,067
<i> You're so insensitive!</i>

354
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:42,300
<i>Hazel, I just want to talk
to Felma and my kids.</i>

355
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:43,933
<i> So that we can also reconcile</i>

356
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:45,733
<i>Just like how you forgave
your siblings.</i>

357
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,333
Why aren't you picking up
the phone, Manuel?

358
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:37,800
Mommy, why do you look so
panicky?

359
00:22:41,233 --> 00:22:42,667
Mom.

360
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,733
How can I talk to Felma?

361
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:19,033
So be it.

362
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:20,933
I'm sorry, Bro.

363
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:22,900
I'm sorry.

364
00:23:23,033 --> 00:23:23,767
It's nothing.

365
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,933
Roviel, I'll get there around
one thirty.

366
00:23:45,433 --> 00:23:46,433
<i> Sure, ma'am.</i>

367
00:23:46,867 --> 00:23:47,800
Okay, thank you.

368
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:07,000
<i> Can I keep my dad's pictures?</i>

369
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:11,667
<i>I will keep it in my room
so you won't see it.</i>

370
00:24:18,433 --> 00:24:19,767
Coleen!

371
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:29,267
Hey!

372
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,633
I thought you wouldn't help me.

373
00:24:33,133 --> 00:24:35,000
I'm glad you came,
I'm so nervous.

374
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:37,567
I came here to stop you.

375
00:24:37,867 --> 00:24:39,600
What?

376
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:41,133
What, get out of my way!

377
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:42,133
No, Bro.

378
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:43,900
Go back to Hazel and Jessica.

379
00:24:44,033 --> 00:24:45,233
Go back to Canada.

380
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:53,500
If you don't want to help me,
then don't!

381
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:54,633
But don't you dare stop me!

382
00:24:54,767 --> 00:24:56,667
Bro, don't do this.

383
00:24:57,767 --> 00:24:59,200
We're good, he's my friend.

384
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:00,867
We're okay. We're okay.

385
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,367
Bro, you can't.

386
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:05,567
You won't see Felma.

387
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:09,967
I just want to talk to her.

388
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,233
No! You can't!

389
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:12,933
- Please, bro.
- Bro, You can't!

390
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:22,900
- Why not? I'll talk to her.
- You can't!

391
00:25:23,033 --> 00:25:25,167
- Bro!
- No matter what happens,

392
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:27,000
even if I have to fight you,
you can't see her!

393
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:28,000
What's your problem?

394
00:25:32,433 --> 00:25:33,233
Manuel?

395
00:25:39,733 --> 00:25:41,233
You've got some nerve!

396
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:43,967
Didn't I tell you not
to see that woman!

397
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:46,167
I've been away from them for
eighteen years!

398
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,433
Can't I see them even for a
minute?

399
00:25:48,567 --> 00:25:50,800
What will come out of that short
meeting you'll have with her?

400
00:25:50,933 --> 00:25:51,933
You're overthinking!

401
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:53,267
Where are you going again?

402
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:57,567
<i>From now on, I won't let you
affect me anymore, Manuel.</i>

403
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:58,367
Love?

404
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,367
Don't tell me you're going to
track him.

405
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:03,867
Mom, you can only use that
if there's an emergency.

406
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,700
This is an emergency.

407
00:26:05,833 --> 00:26:08,533
Now, show me how to use this
tracking app.

408
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:10,300
If you don't, you'll be in big
trouble with me!

409
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:11,833
Felma, wait.
Can we talk?

410
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:13,200
No, I don't want to talk to you.

411
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:15,133
I knew it!

412
00:26:15,267 --> 00:26:16,633
You've got some nerve!

413
00:26:16,767 --> 00:26:18,433
Especially you, you've got no
shame being a mistress!

414
00:26:18,567 --> 00:26:20,167
Here. Here is the mistress.
